public class ReflexiveHashMap<V1,V2>
extends HashMap<V1,V2>

Allows for reflexive Map modification between two recursively mapped values. Each put operation adds the key to an internal HashMap that maps value->key (type ). This class is useful for situations where two values should have an associative relationship rather than a key/value relationship. Note: Like its parent and the rest of the Java Collections Framework, ReflexiveHashMap is not thread safe and must be externally synchronized for concurrent use.

Author:
Brian Groenke
